"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964947","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-09-06","<p>The Foreign Secretary and officials have been in touch with both Governments to express our concern over the dispute and its potential implications. We have and will continue to urge restraint and de-escalation through the appropriate diplomatic channels.</p><p>The Government continues to promote human rights across the Middle East, both bilaterally and with key international partners such as Canada. The UK frequently expresses concerns on human rights issues to Saudi Arabia at the most senior levels. We can only bring about the changes we would like to see by working with countries. We do not shy away from raising legitimate human rights concerns, and we make this point very clearly in public and in private.</p><p>The UK is a close partner to both Canada and Saudi Arabia and enjoys positive and constructive diplomatic relations with both countries. It is in the UK’s interest that we have both public and private conversations on matters of mutual concern.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-09-06T15:53:56.27Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964947/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964947/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964947/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-09-03","Canada and Saudi Arabia: Trade Agreements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with his Canadian counterpart on trade relations between that country and Saudi Arabia; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Jo Swinson","East Dunbartonshire","Jo Swinson","169160"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964948","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-09-06","<p>The Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs and officials have been in touch with both Governments to express our concern over the dispute and its potential implications. We have and will continue to urge restraint and de-escalation through the appropriate diplomatic channels.</p><p>The Government continues to promote human rights across the Middle East, both bilaterally and with key international partners such as Canada. The UK frequently expresses concerns on human rights issues to Saudi Arabia at the most senior levels. We can only bring about the changes we would like to see by working with countries. We do not shy away from raising legitimate human rights concerns, and we make this point very clearly in public and in private.</p><p>The UK is a close partner to both Canada and Saudi Arabia and enjoys positive and constructive diplomatic relations with both countries. It is in the UK’s interest that we have both public and private conversations on matters of mutual concern.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-09-06T15:56:43.797Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964948/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964948/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/964948/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-09-03","Middle East: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps he is taking to support his Canadian counterpart in promoting human rights across the Middle East.","false","Biography information for Jo Swinson","East Dunbartonshire","Jo Swinson","169161"
