"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/947489","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-09-04","<p>The Prime Minister is routinely kept updated on matters of national security which includes nuclear issues. In order not to simplify the calculations of any potential aggressor the UK deliberately does not define precisely when, how and at what scale we would use our nuclear weapons. The decision of the UK to leave the EU will not impact on this approach.</p>","South Staffordshire","Gavin Williamson","168164","2018-09-04T15:08:40.46Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/947489/answer","Biography information for Gavin Williamson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/947489/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/947489/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-07-24","Armed Forces: Deployment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether he has discussed the UK’s first strike policy with the Prime Minister since his appointment; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Alex Norris","Nottingham North","Alex Norris","168163"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/947490","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-09-13","<p>The Department has made representations to the European Commission in writing and in person to discuss the concerns of entertainment venues and lighting designers and potential solutions. Following officials’ advice to the industry, I understand that some of their representatives also met with the Commission and submitted an alternative proposal for stage lighting for their consideration.</p><p> </p><p>It should be noted that this is still a proposal at this stage and a final decision on the draft regulation is likely to be made at the end of this year. Until then we will continue to engage with both industry, other Member States and the European Commission to inform the UK position prior to voting on the regulation.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-09-13T15:12:55.647Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/947490/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/947490/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/947490/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-07-24","Lighting: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what progress his Department is making on taking forward with the European Commission the concerns of entertainment venues and lighting designers about the effect of the proposed EU Lighting Regulation 2020 to replace EU1194/2012 on theatre and other entertainment lighting.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","167943"
